== write_param + commit_params ==

CAUTION: writes modify persistent controller state. Verify on a non-critical
key with a known-recoverable value before automating writes.

host → ctrl  (12 bytes)  write
02 00 00 00  22 00 00 00  0C 01 00 00
^^                                       opcode = 0x02 write_param
   ^^                                    sequence
      ^^                                 aux
         ^^                              pad
            ^^^^^^^^^^^                  key   = 34   (downcam_scale_x)
                         ^^^^^^^^^^^     value = 0x0000010C = 268     (write the same value back to test round-trip)

ctrl → host  (12 bytes)
02 00 00 00  00 00 00 00  00 00 00 00
^^                                       opcode_echo = 0x02

host → ctrl  (4 bytes)  commit
03 00 00 00
^^                                       opcode = 0x03 commit_params

ctrl → host  (4 bytes)
03 00 00 00
^^                                       opcode_echo = 0x03

A write WITHOUT a following commit is silently discarded by the controller
on reset; it is NOT applied. Always commit at the end of a write burst.
